Durban - Residents have been advised to stay indoors and off the roads as heavy rains have been predicted for the next two days. According to the South African Weather Service, heavy rain has been predicted for Thursday and Friday. Rain is expected to fall in Harry Gwala, Ugu, spreading to eThekwini, uMgungundlovu, uMvoti, King Cetshawyo and Ilembe. Heavy rain, which could lead to localised flooding, is expected to fall along the north-east coast and adjacent interior of the Eastern Cape until Friday morning. Localised urban flooding is expected in low lying areas along the South Coast and adjacent interior of the Eastern Cape. The Weather Service further advises people avoid crossing rivers and swollen streams where water is above ankle height. Daily News 